freeglut
------------------------------------------
freeglut is a completely OpenSourced alternative to the OpenGL Utility
Toolkit (GLUT) library. GLUT was originally written by Mark Kilgard to
support the sample programs in the second edition OpenGL 'RedBook'.
Since then, GLUT has been used in a wide variety of practical
applications because it is simple, widely available and highly portable.

GLUT (and hence freeglut) allows the user to create and manage windows
containing OpenGL contexts on a wide range of platforms and also read
the mouse, keyboard and joystick functions.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.19-4
  libGL1-6.4.2-1
  libGLU1-6.4.2-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  cygwin-1.5.18-1
  autoconf2.5-2.59-3
  automake1.9-1.9.6-1
  binutils-20050610-1
  bison-2.1-1
  flex-2.5.4a-4
  gawk-3.1.5-2
  gcc-core-3.4.4-1
  libtool1.5-1.5.20-2
  make-3.80-1
  sed-4.1.4-1

Canonical website:
  http://freeglut.sourceforge.net/

Canonical download:
  http://prdownloads.sourceforge.net/freeglut/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack freeglut-2.4.0-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./freeglut-2.4.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/freeglut-2.4.0-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/freeglut-2.4.0-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/libglut3-2.4.0-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

